1
00:00:04,971 --> 00:00:06,638
In 2026, I, Kosei Neo,

2
00:00:06,639 --> 00:00:10,009
president of NEOXIS,

3
00:00:10,010 --> 00:00:11,910
should have died

4
00:00:11,911 --> 00:00:13,846
<i>when someone</i>

5
00:00:13,847 --> 00:00:14,814
<i>pushed me…</i>

6
00:00:16,549 --> 00:00:18,183
I ended up in the body of Eito Nomoto,

7
00:00:18,184 --> 00:00:20,486
who looked just like me

8
00:00:20,487 --> 00:00:23,522
and was supposed to have died

9
00:00:23,523 --> 00:00:25,491
in an accident in 2012.

10
00:00:25,492 --> 00:00:28,260
He was the son of Eiji Nomoto,
the man caught in my fall.

11
00:00:28,261 --> 00:00:29,729
‎EITO NOMOTO

12
00:00:30,363 --> 00:00:32,965
After signing an advisor contract
with NEOXIS,

13
00:00:32,966 --> 00:00:34,767
I opposed the Olympics venture

14
00:00:34,768 --> 00:00:37,469
and the Vena Bank acquisition,

15
00:00:37,470 --> 00:00:38,938
<i>but no one would listen.</i>

16
00:00:39,506 --> 00:00:42,509
<i>But they can't make it!
No. 8 Daiichi Helios holds on to win!</i>

17
00:00:43,109 --> 00:00:45,412
Had living as Eito

18
00:00:46,379 --> 00:00:48,248
changed the future?

19
00:00:49,249 --> 00:00:51,417
My ability was doubted,

20
00:00:51,418 --> 00:00:53,018
and I was fired.

21
00:00:53,019 --> 00:00:54,788
CONGRATS! SARASA IKETANI
GOLD AWARD

22
00:00:55,955 --> 00:00:58,123
<i>I felt jealous of Kosei Neo</i>

23
00:00:58,124 --> 00:01:00,460
for supporting Sarasa, but…

24
00:01:01,494 --> 00:01:03,662
<i>Kosei Neo had reached out</i>

25
00:01:03,663 --> 00:01:06,399
<i>to help the shopping street.</i>

26
00:01:06,966 --> 00:01:08,568
So he really can see

27
00:01:09,202 --> 00:01:10,970
the future?

28
00:01:14,674 --> 00:01:17,409
Even though so many things have changed…

29
00:01:17,410 --> 00:01:18,343
‎THE HISTORY WHICH EITO HAS CHANGED

30
00:01:18,344 --> 00:01:20,613
…by my living as Eito Nomoto,

31
00:01:21,548 --> 00:01:22,714
can the eviction…

32
00:01:22,715 --> 00:01:24,149
‎THE UNCHANGING CRISIS FACING
‎THE SHOPPING STREET

33
00:01:24,150 --> 00:01:26,686
…the most critical part of the history,
still not be changed?

34
00:01:28,188 --> 00:01:30,123
<i>March 2020.</i>

35
00:01:31,091 --> 00:01:34,259
<i>COVID disrupted everyday life.</i>

36
00:01:34,260 --> 00:01:35,528
AKARI-NU

37
00:01:41,434 --> 00:01:42,535
IKETANI PRINTING FACTORY

38
00:01:45,138 --> 00:01:48,574
Can we have Sarasa's art
printed on a mask?

39
00:01:48,575 --> 00:01:52,311
Leave it to me. It's a piece of cake!

40
00:01:52,312 --> 00:01:54,079
It's done, Eito.

41
00:01:54,080 --> 00:01:55,515
- Is this okay?
- Huh?

42
00:01:58,585 --> 00:01:59,552
Oh.

43
00:02:00,720 --> 00:02:01,955
Brilliant.

44
00:02:03,256 --> 00:02:05,124
You're an idiot
who actually gets things done.

45
00:02:05,125 --> 00:02:06,024
Come on…

46
00:02:06,025 --> 00:02:08,460
Could you maybe compliment us differently?

47
00:02:08,461 --> 00:02:10,762
So what are you planning
to do with all this?

48
00:02:10,763 --> 00:02:11,698
Yeah.

49
00:02:13,700 --> 00:02:14,968
IKETANI PRINTING FACTORY

50
00:02:16,569 --> 00:02:18,437
"Don't Let COVID Win!"

51
00:02:18,438 --> 00:02:20,506
"Mass Production Plan
for Original Merchandise!"

52
00:02:20,507 --> 00:02:22,207
I want to produce as much as possible.

53
00:02:22,208 --> 00:02:24,943
I get the masks,

54
00:02:24,944 --> 00:02:26,579
but will the rest actually sell?

55
00:02:27,147 --> 00:02:28,313
People are most terrified

56
00:02:28,314 --> 00:02:30,616
of droplet transmission.

57
00:02:30,617 --> 00:02:32,484
So acrylic dividers

58
00:02:32,485 --> 00:02:33,952
and face shields will sell.

59
00:02:33,953 --> 00:02:37,089
Well, if Eito says so,
I'll take his word for it.

60
00:02:37,090 --> 00:02:39,024
But these gloves…

61
00:02:39,025 --> 00:02:42,461
People will start
fearing contact transmission too.

62
00:02:42,462 --> 00:02:45,797
They'll start being used
in hospitals and at mealtimes.

63
00:02:45,798 --> 00:02:48,334
I see.

64
00:02:49,602 --> 00:02:51,371
With the Olympics postponed,

65
00:02:51,938 --> 00:02:55,275
every deal we pursued
as a partner company is cancelled.

66
00:02:55,875 --> 00:02:57,843
The damage is too severe.

67
00:02:57,844 --> 00:03:00,312
As head of finance,

68
00:03:00,313 --> 00:03:01,181
I find this painful.

69
00:03:02,048 --> 00:03:04,083
We should have listened to Eito.

70
00:03:04,651 --> 00:03:07,753
President Neo will figure something out.

71
00:03:07,754 --> 00:03:10,523
He's the man
who foresaw Trump's victory, after all.

72
00:03:13,526 --> 00:03:16,462
We still haven't received
any instructions from the president?

73
00:03:17,096 --> 00:03:20,032
He's been holed up in his penthouse.

74
00:03:20,033 --> 00:03:23,503
<i>He's probably thinking ahead
and mapping out the best strategy.</i>

75
00:03:39,819 --> 00:03:41,453
What should be done

76
00:03:41,454 --> 00:03:43,156
about NEOXIS's crisis?

77
00:03:44,490 --> 00:03:45,325
Yes.

78
00:03:46,526 --> 00:03:47,627
Shouldn't that be up

79
00:03:49,162 --> 00:03:53,198
to President Neo, the one who fired me?

80
00:03:53,199 --> 00:03:56,435
That's true,

81
00:03:56,436 --> 00:03:58,971
but whether it's because
of Olympic setback or something else,

82
00:03:58,972 --> 00:04:01,674
he's been in his room for a week.

83
00:04:02,475 --> 00:04:03,443
<i>That's strange.</i>

84
00:04:04,410 --> 00:04:06,211
<i>The old Kosei Neo</i>

85
00:04:06,212 --> 00:04:10,282
<i>rebounded fast
with home-focused businesses.</i>

86
00:04:10,283 --> 00:04:11,516
<i>So why now?</i>

87
00:04:11,517 --> 00:04:14,187
I want to devote myself
to NEOXIS's growth.

88
00:04:15,054 --> 00:04:18,190
<i>Could learning
of President Ichimanda's goodwill</i>

89
00:04:18,191 --> 00:04:22,095
<i>have sapped his will
to climb by crushing Soman?</i>

90
00:04:22,662 --> 00:04:25,598
<i>Or is he lovesick over Sarasa?</i>

91
00:04:26,899 --> 00:04:27,734
<i>No…</i>

92
00:04:28,568 --> 00:04:31,938
I understand your feelings
about President Neo,

93
00:04:32,538 --> 00:04:34,573
but NEOXIS is in a crisis.

94
00:04:34,574 --> 00:04:36,942
If the company fails,

95
00:04:36,943 --> 00:04:40,013
countless employees and their families
will have nowhere to turn.

96
00:04:44,117 --> 00:04:46,452
People have vanished from the streets.

97
00:04:50,790 --> 00:04:53,760
So where is everyone now?

98
00:05:00,733 --> 00:05:02,402
Not outside…

99
00:05:03,369 --> 00:05:04,637
Inside their homes?

100
00:05:06,539 --> 00:05:07,373
Yes.

101
00:05:18,785 --> 00:05:20,686
What a coincidence.

102
00:05:20,687 --> 00:05:22,588
I was thinking the exact same thing.

103
00:05:25,291 --> 00:05:26,926
This is our opportunity.

104
00:05:27,727 --> 00:05:29,429
Let's launch a new venture.

105
00:05:37,303 --> 00:05:40,372
We're already working on expanding
streaming and remote services.

106
00:05:40,373 --> 00:05:41,973
We're also preparing

107
00:05:41,974 --> 00:05:44,376
to expand delivery operations,
focusing on food.

108
00:05:44,377 --> 00:05:47,413
Securing PCR test kits
is also going smoothly.

109
00:05:48,114 --> 00:05:49,482
"For the People"

110
00:05:50,016 --> 00:05:52,385
is moving along well
even in the midst of the pandemic.

111
00:05:53,152 --> 00:05:56,288
If people won't go out,
target them at home.

112
00:05:56,289 --> 00:05:59,258
Your foresight
never ceases to amaze me, sir.

113
00:06:02,261 --> 00:06:04,831
As long as I'm here,

114
00:06:06,999 --> 00:06:08,267
NEOXIS will never fall.

115
00:06:13,706 --> 00:06:16,608
The governor of Tokyo is saying to avoid

116
00:06:16,609 --> 00:06:19,779
crowded indoor spaces
and to limit unnecessary outings.

117
00:06:20,580 --> 00:06:23,882
Customers are going
to stop coming altogether.

118
00:06:23,883 --> 00:06:25,984
And the Spring Koshien tournament
is cancelled too.

119
00:06:25,985 --> 00:06:28,553
The shopping street's spring festival

120
00:06:28,554 --> 00:06:30,021
probably isn't happening this year.

121
00:06:30,022 --> 00:06:32,023
It feels so lonely.

122
00:06:32,024 --> 00:06:34,993
But with some shops closing down,

123
00:06:34,994 --> 00:06:37,095
I'm grateful that

124
00:06:37,096 --> 00:06:38,865
we're holding on thanks to Eito.

125
00:06:39,532 --> 00:06:42,167
Orders for the COVID supplies
are flooding in

126
00:06:42,168 --> 00:06:44,069
faster than we can produce them.

127
00:06:44,070 --> 00:06:46,471
And riding that wave,
our frozen Akari croquettes

128
00:06:46,472 --> 00:06:49,541
and cutlets are selling through the roof.

129
00:06:49,542 --> 00:06:53,311
Yeah!

130
00:06:53,312 --> 00:06:54,813
But eventually,

131
00:06:54,814 --> 00:06:57,983
other suppliers will start
making masks and acrylic dividers.

132
00:06:57,984 --> 00:06:59,751
We can only make profit now.

133
00:06:59,752 --> 00:07:01,421
We need to plan ahead.

134
00:07:01,988 --> 00:07:03,321
Now that a state of emergency

135
00:07:03,322 --> 00:07:05,690
has been declared in Tokyo,

136
00:07:05,691 --> 00:07:07,426
we have to get through this together.

137
00:07:07,427 --> 00:07:08,327
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

138
00:07:11,197 --> 00:07:12,297
Oh!

139
00:07:12,298 --> 00:07:13,666
- Huh?
- What's wrong, Eito?

140
00:07:14,667 --> 00:07:17,502
<i>That's when it hit me.</i>

141
00:07:17,503 --> 00:07:20,105
<i>I remembered a morning
from my past life as Kosei Neo,</i>

142
00:07:20,106 --> 00:07:22,741
<i>waking up hungover.</i>

143
00:07:22,742 --> 00:07:23,875
Sir.

144
00:07:23,876 --> 00:07:25,644
Good morning.

145
00:07:25,645 --> 00:07:27,814
Breakfast is ready.

146
00:07:28,681 --> 00:07:31,584
<i>The suspicion
of a forbidden night with Eri.</i>

147
00:07:32,151 --> 00:07:33,485
<i>I'd been drinking heavily</i>

148
00:07:33,486 --> 00:07:36,122
<i>the night
the state of emergency was declared.</i>

149
00:07:37,190 --> 00:07:38,490
- Huh?
- What?

150
00:07:38,491 --> 00:07:39,959
Sorry.

151
00:07:40,493 --> 00:07:42,160
- Something just came to mind.
- Huh?

152
00:07:42,161 --> 00:07:43,762
- Hey, Eito!
- Eito!

153
00:07:43,763 --> 00:07:45,297
- Eito!
- Sorry!

154
00:07:45,298 --> 00:07:46,899
A non-essential outing!

155
00:07:51,771 --> 00:07:53,973
<i>That said, staking out a building…</i>

156
00:07:56,175 --> 00:07:58,144
<i>What am I even doing?</i>

157
00:08:02,415 --> 00:08:03,249
Eito?

158
00:08:04,517 --> 00:08:05,584
Oh, Tomono!

159
00:08:05,585 --> 00:08:07,185
What are you doing out here?

160
00:08:07,186 --> 00:08:09,755
I just happened to be passing by…

161
00:08:11,057 --> 00:08:14,092
By the way, how has NEOXIS been doing?

162
00:08:14,093 --> 00:08:17,530
Thanks to you,
we may just get through this crisis.

163
00:08:18,331 --> 00:08:21,234
How is President Neo doing?

164
00:08:21,868 --> 00:08:25,303
He's driving the staff harder than ever.

165
00:08:25,304 --> 00:08:28,808
I wonder if that is wise?

166
00:08:29,742 --> 00:08:32,043
I'm asking you specifically, Tomono…

167
00:08:32,044 --> 00:08:34,046
How is President Neo regarded these days?

168
00:08:34,747 --> 00:08:36,782
Could he be making enemies
among the staff?

169
00:08:38,518 --> 00:08:41,586
There may be people who feel that way…

170
00:08:41,587 --> 00:08:42,921
Like whom?

171
00:08:42,922 --> 00:08:44,590
<i>Tsuchiya? Takarabe?</i>

172
00:08:45,625 --> 00:08:48,393
They struggle
with his demanding directive…

173
00:08:48,394 --> 00:08:49,362
But is there a reason?

174
00:08:50,396 --> 00:08:52,732
No, I was just a little worried.

175
00:08:57,436 --> 00:08:59,839
- Oh!
- Wait!

176
00:09:01,240 --> 00:09:02,208
Wait!

177
00:09:05,912 --> 00:09:08,413
- Over there!
- Huh?

178
00:09:08,414 --> 00:09:09,347
- Wait!
- Sorry!

179
00:09:09,348 --> 00:09:11,216
- No…
- Sorry!

180
00:09:11,217 --> 00:09:12,450
Sorry for the close contact.

181
00:09:12,451 --> 00:09:13,518
- No problem!
- Sorry!

182
00:09:13,519 --> 00:09:15,755
- Yes?
- Stay here!

183
00:09:16,289 --> 00:09:17,123
Just…

184
00:09:17,623 --> 00:09:18,890
- Huh?
- Huh?

185
00:09:18,891 --> 00:09:20,025
Huh?

186
00:09:20,026 --> 00:09:22,295
<i>Could this be the night
of their forbidden encounter?</i>

187
00:09:22,929 --> 00:09:24,963
<i>She's going to stay in that room
until morning?</i>

188
00:09:24,964 --> 00:09:28,667
<i>No!</i>

189
00:09:28,668 --> 00:09:30,001
No! This can't happen!

190
00:09:30,002 --> 00:09:31,369
Are you all right?

191
00:09:31,370 --> 00:09:32,771
I mean…

192
00:09:32,772 --> 00:09:34,906
My little sister just went alone

193
00:09:34,907 --> 00:09:36,141
into a man's room.

194
00:09:36,142 --> 00:09:38,109
<i>What if something happens?</i>

195
00:09:38,110 --> 00:09:39,644
<i>Given the circumstances, you know…</i>

196
00:09:39,645 --> 00:09:40,646
That would never happen.

197
00:09:41,213 --> 00:09:42,982
How can you be so sure?

198
00:09:43,549 --> 00:09:45,818
Because Eri would never betray me.

199
00:09:46,419 --> 00:09:47,720
What?

200
00:09:48,287 --> 00:09:49,322
The truth is,

201
00:09:50,122 --> 00:09:52,458
I've been seeing your sister.

202
00:09:54,961 --> 00:09:56,696
We've also promised to get married.

203
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:01,867
You…

204
00:10:02,635 --> 00:10:05,104
intend to marry Eri?

205
00:10:06,005 --> 00:10:07,472
- You're seeing her?
- Yes!

206
00:10:07,473 --> 00:10:10,342
I mean…

207
00:10:10,343 --> 00:10:11,776
That's wonderful!

208
00:10:11,777 --> 00:10:13,411
- Congrats!
- Thank you!

209
00:10:13,412 --> 00:10:15,648
- Yes!
- Yes.

210
00:10:16,415 --> 00:10:19,251
As you said, she's back.

211
00:10:19,852 --> 00:10:22,320
So are you two going to meet up?

212
00:10:22,321 --> 00:10:23,455
Want to go?

213
00:10:23,456 --> 00:10:24,589
Want to go meet up?

214
00:10:24,590 --> 00:10:25,690
- Yes.
- Let's go!

215
00:10:25,691 --> 00:10:26,658
Yes!

216
00:10:26,659 --> 00:10:28,293
What?

217
00:10:28,294 --> 00:10:29,628
Yeah…

218
00:10:29,629 --> 00:10:31,997
Wait, what are you two doing here?

219
00:10:31,998 --> 00:10:34,199
What are you doing out at this hour?

220
00:10:34,200 --> 00:10:36,434
I came to get some urgent documents.

221
00:10:36,435 --> 00:10:38,737
I need to have them finished
by tomorrow morning.

222
00:10:38,738 --> 00:10:40,071
Then I'll help you.

223
00:10:40,072 --> 00:10:41,574
- Thanks.
- Oh.

224
00:10:42,375 --> 00:10:44,442
Finish them up together,

225
00:10:44,443 --> 00:10:46,378
you two.

226
00:10:46,379 --> 00:10:48,279
You seem awfully happy about something.

227
00:10:48,280 --> 00:10:49,749
Just finish them up.

228
00:10:50,316 --> 00:10:51,383
Well then.

229
00:10:51,384 --> 00:10:52,817
See you.

230
00:10:52,818 --> 00:10:53,985
- See you.
- Yeah.

231
00:10:53,986 --> 00:10:54,820
Yeah.

232
00:10:56,689 --> 00:10:58,658
<i>What a perfect night.</i>

233
00:11:02,628 --> 00:11:03,663
Ah!

234
00:11:15,941 --> 00:11:17,677
<i>Why is Sarasa here too?</i>

235
00:11:25,718 --> 00:11:26,552
No way…

236
00:11:31,157 --> 00:11:32,491
She went to the top floor.

237
00:11:33,526 --> 00:11:35,361
To Kosei Neo's room?

238
00:11:45,071 --> 00:11:46,105
Why?

239
00:11:54,046 --> 00:11:54,880
<i>No.</i>

240
00:11:56,148 --> 00:11:58,050
<i>Sarasa isn't like that.</i>

241
00:11:59,218 --> 00:12:02,822
<i>Trust her.</i>

242
00:12:05,024 --> 00:12:05,990
You scared me!

243
00:12:05,991 --> 00:12:08,326
Hey. What are you doing?

244
00:12:08,327 --> 00:12:11,062
Oh, I just happened to be here.

245
00:12:11,063 --> 00:12:12,832
What about you?

246
00:12:13,566 --> 00:12:15,500
President Neo emailed me.

247
00:12:15,501 --> 00:12:18,938
He wanted to buy one of my paintings,
so I just dropped it off.

248
00:12:19,538 --> 00:12:21,841
Oh, really…

249
00:12:23,676 --> 00:12:27,713
It makes me happy
when someone appreciates my work.

250
00:12:30,149 --> 00:12:32,183
Let's head back together.

251
00:12:32,184 --> 00:12:33,018
Sure.

252
00:12:38,691 --> 00:12:39,859
<i>But wait.</i>

253
00:12:40,960 --> 00:12:43,461
<i>Even if I trust Sarasa,</i>

254
00:12:43,462 --> 00:12:46,632
<i>I can't dismiss
Kosei Neo's feelings for her.</i>

255
00:12:48,400 --> 00:12:49,502
<i>In other words,</i>

256
00:12:50,269 --> 00:12:52,138
<i>my rival in love</i>

257
00:12:52,938 --> 00:12:54,240
<i>is myself?</i>

258
00:13:09,688 --> 00:13:13,191
I'm truly impressed by your foresight
to revive the shopping street

259
00:13:13,192 --> 00:13:14,425
with COVID supplies

260
00:13:14,426 --> 00:13:18,329
and to advise NEOXIS

261
00:13:18,330 --> 00:13:19,932
on the home-based business.

262
00:13:20,866 --> 00:13:22,868
I thought you'd written me off

263
00:13:23,569 --> 00:13:24,969
after my horse racing prediction failed.

264
00:13:24,970 --> 00:13:26,071
No,

265
00:13:27,606 --> 00:13:30,042
in fact, I'm hoping for your guidance.

266
00:13:32,011 --> 00:13:34,213
- What?
- I've always believed

267
00:13:34,847 --> 00:13:37,249
connecting people

268
00:13:38,317 --> 00:13:40,986
enriches the world.

269
00:13:42,054 --> 00:13:43,121
That's why

270
00:13:43,122 --> 00:13:45,758
<i>I built ties with Soman.</i>

271
00:13:46,425 --> 00:13:47,960
But COVID is pushing the world

272
00:13:49,128 --> 00:13:51,730
in the opposite direction.

273
00:13:52,598 --> 00:13:55,367
People can change dramatically
depending on their circumstances.

274
00:13:56,202 --> 00:13:57,870
It's bleak.

275
00:13:59,038 --> 00:14:02,441
The travel companies
and hotels I've backed

276
00:14:03,309 --> 00:14:06,445
are in a nightmare of losses,
and their stock prices have collapsed.

277
00:14:07,680 --> 00:14:10,049
Tell me

278
00:14:10,716 --> 00:14:11,884
if there's a way to recover.

279
00:14:15,054 --> 00:14:16,989
I won't ask for free, of course.

280
00:14:18,424 --> 00:14:20,726
I'm prepared to bring you on

281
00:14:21,227 --> 00:14:22,928
at a generous salary.

282
00:14:25,197 --> 00:14:27,199
From being fired by NEOXIS

283
00:14:28,100 --> 00:14:29,501
to joining Togo Fund?

284
00:14:32,404 --> 00:14:33,906
The shopping street

285
00:14:34,940 --> 00:14:36,709
needs a backer too, doesn't it?

286
00:14:43,048 --> 00:14:45,351
I want to save Akari Shopping Street.

287
00:14:46,418 --> 00:14:48,320
Will you promise to help?

288
00:14:49,221 --> 00:14:50,189
Yeah.

289
00:14:52,524 --> 00:14:56,661
The stock of the company
that develops a COVID vaccine

290
00:14:56,662 --> 00:14:57,930
will skyrocket.

291
00:14:59,331 --> 00:15:02,401
Which company is that?

292
00:15:06,238 --> 00:15:07,939
I see.

293
00:15:07,940 --> 00:15:09,974
Top foreign security guys

294
00:15:09,975 --> 00:15:12,343
really do think differently.

295
00:15:12,344 --> 00:15:13,845
But there are

296
00:15:13,846 --> 00:15:16,515
so many pharmaceutical companies
out there.

297
00:15:17,283 --> 00:15:20,386
We'd be glad if you could tell us.

298
00:15:22,121 --> 00:15:24,022
There is some

299
00:15:24,023 --> 00:15:26,824
compelling information I could share…

300
00:15:26,825 --> 00:15:29,328
- Um, which company is it?
- Which company is it?

301
00:15:31,030 --> 00:15:34,233
It's classified
at a national security level.

302
00:15:36,101 --> 00:15:38,470
Can you swear you won't tell a soul?

303
00:15:39,038 --> 00:15:40,139
You have my word.

304
00:15:42,007 --> 00:15:42,907
NOMOTO DRY CLEANERS

305
00:15:42,908 --> 00:15:44,509
A lavish spread today.

306
00:15:44,510 --> 00:15:47,011
More gifts from President Neo

307
00:15:47,012 --> 00:15:49,113
that Eri brought over. Here you go.

308
00:15:49,114 --> 00:15:50,114
- Oh.
- Here.

309
00:15:50,115 --> 00:15:53,886
Shall we get started, then?

310
00:15:55,187 --> 00:15:57,422
Sorry! We have a surprise!

311
00:15:57,423 --> 00:15:58,323
A surprise?

312
00:15:58,324 --> 00:16:00,892
Please welcome today's guests of honor!

313
00:16:00,893 --> 00:16:02,460
Guests of honor?

314
00:16:02,461 --> 00:16:04,363
Start the music!

315
00:16:13,405 --> 00:16:14,406
Um…

316
00:16:15,107 --> 00:16:18,876
The Akari Shopping Street's little sister,

317
00:16:18,877 --> 00:16:21,145
Eri Nomoto,

318
00:16:21,146 --> 00:16:24,649
and her wonderful partner,

319
00:16:24,650 --> 00:16:26,819
Tatsuki Tomono,

320
00:16:28,153 --> 00:16:30,189
are engaged!

321
00:16:31,423 --> 00:16:33,358
Congrats!

322
00:16:33,359 --> 00:16:34,859
Eri is engaged?

323
00:16:34,860 --> 00:16:36,361
Everyone knew?

324
00:16:36,362 --> 00:16:37,963
- You all knew?!
- Yeah!

325
00:16:38,831 --> 00:16:40,164
Hey!

326
00:16:40,165 --> 00:16:41,933
Today is a day to celebrate.

327
00:16:41,934 --> 00:16:44,702
You two, take off your masks
and show us your faces!

328
00:16:44,703 --> 00:16:45,737
- Yeah!
- Yeah!

329
00:16:45,738 --> 00:16:47,372
Hey! Kamaitachi!

330
00:16:47,373 --> 00:16:49,207
I mean guys! You can take your masks off!

331
00:16:49,208 --> 00:16:50,609
- Yeah!
- Yeah!

332
00:16:55,981 --> 00:16:57,683
This is completely out of order!

333
00:16:58,584 --> 00:17:01,487
I'm her father, and I'm the last to know?!

334
00:17:02,921 --> 00:17:04,455
I refuse to accept this!

335
00:17:04,456 --> 00:17:06,057
No, wait…

336
00:17:06,058 --> 00:17:08,893
I'm sorry. I thought you'd be happy.

337
00:17:08,894 --> 00:17:10,529
Please forgive me!

338
00:17:12,898 --> 00:17:13,866
No,

339
00:17:14,900 --> 00:17:16,535
I just always wanted to say that.

340
00:17:17,236 --> 00:17:19,604
It's the kind of thing
a father of the bride would say…

341
00:17:19,605 --> 00:17:21,105
Come on!

342
00:17:21,106 --> 00:17:23,074
Cut it out!

343
00:17:23,075 --> 00:17:25,643
That's right.

344
00:17:25,644 --> 00:17:26,912
When I think back…

345
00:17:28,013 --> 00:17:29,348
29 years ago,

346
00:17:30,416 --> 00:17:33,752
when Eri was born,
she was just so precious.

347
00:17:34,453 --> 00:17:37,423
I'll never forget the look
on her mother's face.

348
00:17:40,059 --> 00:17:40,893
That…

349
00:17:41,927 --> 00:17:43,362
my precious daughter

350
00:17:45,164 --> 00:17:47,399
and someone as wonderful as you, Tomono…

351
00:17:48,901 --> 00:17:51,803
I don't know how to thank you…

352
00:17:51,804 --> 00:17:54,440
- You're killing me.
- Yeah.

353
00:17:56,708 --> 00:17:58,243
Now

354
00:17:58,811 --> 00:18:01,279
for the flower presentation!

355
00:18:01,280 --> 00:18:03,315
- Okay.
- Okay.

356
00:18:05,551 --> 00:18:06,684
- Congrats!
- Congrats!

357
00:18:06,685 --> 00:18:08,420
- Thank you.
- Congrats!

358
00:18:15,961 --> 00:18:17,795
Great!

359
00:18:17,796 --> 00:18:20,332
Isn't it great, Eiji?

360
00:18:22,267 --> 00:18:23,502
This is the best day ever!

361
00:18:27,940 --> 00:18:29,774
Sarasa! Hey!

362
00:18:29,775 --> 00:18:31,709
- Sarasa! Come here!
- Huh?

363
00:18:31,710 --> 00:18:33,878
- Sarasa! Eito!
- Huh?

364
00:18:33,879 --> 00:18:35,147
- Oh?
- Huh?

365
00:18:35,781 --> 00:18:37,548
You should be next,

366
00:18:37,549 --> 00:18:39,083
don't you think?

367
00:18:39,084 --> 00:18:41,452
- Right.
- You tell them!

368
00:18:41,453 --> 00:18:43,155
I mean, that would be wonderful, but…

369
00:18:43,722 --> 00:18:46,557
How many years are you going
to keep her waiting?

370
00:18:46,558 --> 00:18:48,226
- Yeah!
- Yeah!

371
00:18:48,227 --> 00:18:49,061
Right?

372
00:18:50,662 --> 00:18:51,497
Yeah…

373
00:18:52,664 --> 00:18:54,398
Say something!

374
00:18:54,399 --> 00:18:56,134
Say something, Eito!

375
00:18:56,135 --> 00:18:59,637
Thanks for today!

376
00:18:59,638 --> 00:19:03,808
Congrats!

377
00:19:03,809 --> 00:19:04,775
Eito!

378
00:19:04,776 --> 00:19:05,977
Good night!

379
00:19:05,978 --> 00:19:07,011
- Good night!
- Good night!

380
00:19:07,012 --> 00:19:08,713
- Good night!
- Okay!

381
00:19:08,714 --> 00:19:10,515
- See you!
- Oh!

382
00:19:10,516 --> 00:19:11,949
- See you!
- Thank you for today.

383
00:19:11,950 --> 00:19:14,085
Thank you too.

384
00:19:14,086 --> 00:19:16,054
Could I have a moment?

385
00:19:18,123 --> 00:19:20,259
You were right, Eito.

386
00:19:21,660 --> 00:19:25,229
As a condition
of the Vena Bank acquisition,

387
00:19:25,230 --> 00:19:27,098
Vena Holdings, which is aiming

388
00:19:27,099 --> 00:19:29,735
to expand in Japan, is demanding
a large plot of land in Tokyo.

389
00:19:30,802 --> 00:19:31,803
Just as I thought.

390
00:19:32,671 --> 00:19:35,741
The top candidates are

391
00:19:36,375 --> 00:19:39,678
the Akari Housing Complex
and Akari Shopping Street.

392
00:19:43,448 --> 00:19:45,550
I objected,

393
00:19:45,551 --> 00:19:47,652
but Tsuchiya and Takarabe insist

394
00:19:47,653 --> 00:19:51,088
it's the best match

395
00:19:51,089 --> 00:19:52,090
for what Vena wants.

396
00:19:53,192 --> 00:19:54,159
And President Neo?

397
00:19:55,260 --> 00:19:56,395
I believe

398
00:19:57,930 --> 00:20:00,566
he'll protect the shopping street.

399
00:20:01,266 --> 00:20:03,001
What makes you think that?

400
00:20:03,569 --> 00:20:06,637
The painting President Neo
bought from Sarasa

401
00:20:06,638 --> 00:20:08,740
was a painting of the shopping street.

402
00:20:24,456 --> 00:20:26,758
AKARI CROQUETTES
AKARI MINCED MEAT CUTLETS

403
00:20:27,492 --> 00:20:31,797
WELCOME TO AKARI SHOPPING STREET

404
00:20:32,531 --> 00:20:35,801
CONGRATS! SARASA IKETANI
GOLD AWARD

405
00:20:46,078 --> 00:20:47,111
PREVIOUS LIFE ON JULY 9TH, 2022

406
00:20:47,112 --> 00:20:49,513
<i>Fearing Soman,</i>

407
00:20:49,514 --> 00:20:52,316
<i>I had convinced myself
that evicting the shopping street</i>

408
00:20:52,317 --> 00:20:56,120
<i>was the only way
to protect employees and their families.</i>

409
00:20:56,121 --> 00:20:58,256
<i>Following the death
of former Prime Minister Shinzo Abe,</i>

410
00:20:58,257 --> 00:21:01,459
<i>who was shot during a campaign speech…</i>

411
00:21:01,460 --> 00:21:03,794
<i>On July 9th, 2022,</i>

412
00:21:03,795 --> 00:21:07,498
<i>when that news broke,</i>

413
00:21:07,499 --> 00:21:09,267
<i>the plan to acquire
the Akari Housing Complex</i>

414
00:21:09,268 --> 00:21:12,904
<i>and Akari Shopping Street was finalized.</i>

415
00:21:29,421 --> 00:21:32,658
<i>Is this really the price
for using my past-life memories?</i>

416
00:21:36,028 --> 00:21:37,261
Are you all right?

417
00:21:37,262 --> 00:21:38,764
Yes, I'm okay.

418
00:21:39,464 --> 00:21:42,366
Maybe you should go home and rest today.

419
00:21:42,367 --> 00:21:43,201
No,

420
00:21:44,269 --> 00:21:46,171
Ichimanda is waiting.

421
00:21:47,039 --> 00:21:48,073
Let's go.

422
00:21:51,743 --> 00:21:54,078
I'd heard they were demanding
a large plot of land

423
00:21:54,079 --> 00:21:58,215
in Tokyo for the Vena Bank acquisition…

424
00:21:58,216 --> 00:22:00,786
I never imagined the Akari Shopping Street
would be a candidate.

425
00:22:01,887 --> 00:22:05,056
That's precisely why I'm asking

426
00:22:05,057 --> 00:22:06,825
if there's another option.

427
00:22:08,327 --> 00:22:09,828
It's a tough ask.

428
00:22:10,529 --> 00:22:13,431
Land prices in Tokyo
keep rising ahead of the Olympics.

429
00:22:13,432 --> 00:22:15,299
Do you remember saying

430
00:22:15,300 --> 00:22:17,935
you'd spare no effort in supporting

431
00:22:17,936 --> 00:22:19,036
the shopping street?

432
00:22:19,037 --> 00:22:22,607
Of course. I'll do what I can,

433
00:22:23,408 --> 00:22:25,410
but the question is
how President Neo will take it.

434
00:22:26,545 --> 00:22:27,913
Something happened between you two?

435
00:22:28,480 --> 00:22:32,016
President Ichimanda

436
00:22:32,017 --> 00:22:34,385
introduced
the Olympic partnership contacts

437
00:22:34,386 --> 00:22:37,356
and Vena Bank connections
as a way to make amends, but…

438
00:22:37,923 --> 00:22:41,827
He suspects some ulterior motive,

439
00:22:42,594 --> 00:22:44,696
and the tension between us remains.

440
00:22:45,597 --> 00:22:48,467
<i>In other words, he only trusts himself.</i>

441
00:22:50,135 --> 00:22:52,170
<i>That's Kosei Neo.</i>

442
00:22:53,772 --> 00:22:55,239
<i>The day the delayed</i>

443
00:22:55,240 --> 00:22:59,043
<i>Tokyo Olympics opening ceremony
was drawing near…</i>

444
00:22:59,044 --> 00:23:01,679
There's been a major disaster in Atami.

445
00:23:01,680 --> 00:23:03,682
NEOXIS should respond immediately.

446
00:23:06,485 --> 00:23:09,954
Can I be put in charge
of the relief operation plan?

447
00:23:09,955 --> 00:23:11,256
That won't be necessary.

448
00:23:12,491 --> 00:23:13,325
What?

449
00:23:15,093 --> 00:23:16,627
Right now,

450
00:23:16,628 --> 00:23:19,398
let's focus everything
on the Vena Bank acquisition.

451
00:23:22,701 --> 00:23:24,736
Are you serious, sir?

452
00:23:27,439 --> 00:23:29,508
Our relief staff are standing by.

453
00:23:31,843 --> 00:23:32,778
Tomono.

454
00:23:35,647 --> 00:23:36,815
NEOXIS

455
00:23:37,916 --> 00:23:40,452
was built on disaster relief.

456
00:23:41,019 --> 00:23:43,054
"For the People"
is our founding principle, right?

457
00:23:43,822 --> 00:23:44,756
Now is the time

458
00:23:45,457 --> 00:23:47,859
to expand NEOXIS's future.

459
00:23:49,127 --> 00:23:50,262
That will ultimately lead…

460
00:23:52,464 --> 00:23:55,300
to a greater "For the People."

461
00:23:58,003 --> 00:23:59,004
All I hear

462
00:23:59,905 --> 00:24:02,641
is you abandoning our principles.

463
00:24:08,980 --> 00:24:10,248
Are you criticizing me,

464
00:24:12,651 --> 00:24:14,753
Tomono?

465
00:24:19,724 --> 00:24:22,194
I'll go to the disaster zone myself
if I have to.

466
00:24:29,234 --> 00:24:30,602
Good news, Eito!

467
00:24:31,636 --> 00:24:34,172
I found some land for Vena Holdings.

468
00:24:34,873 --> 00:24:36,174
Thank you!

469
00:24:36,675 --> 00:24:39,511
It's a 100,000㎡ plot in Toyosu,

470
00:24:41,179 --> 00:24:44,583
and the rights belong
to President Shijo of Shijo Corporation.

471
00:24:45,984 --> 00:24:47,085
<i>Perfect.</i>

472
00:24:47,886 --> 00:24:51,655
<i>Shijo has been advising NEOXIS
since its founding.</i>

473
00:24:51,656 --> 00:24:52,891
<i>A nice guy.</i>

474
00:24:53,458 --> 00:24:54,893
<i>A trustworthy man.</i>

475
00:24:56,361 --> 00:24:57,795
I thought Neo

476
00:24:57,796 --> 00:25:00,598
could negotiate it,

477
00:25:00,599 --> 00:25:01,933
but the problem is Neo says

478
00:25:02,968 --> 00:25:04,903
he doesn't want to meet him.

479
00:25:05,737 --> 00:25:07,005
What do you mean?

480
00:25:07,772 --> 00:25:08,940
Did something happen?

481
00:25:09,774 --> 00:25:10,775
Possibly.

482
00:25:12,277 --> 00:25:13,979
What a waste of an opportunity.

483
00:25:15,113 --> 00:25:17,415
Why don't you go instead?

484
00:25:18,450 --> 00:25:19,650
What?

485
00:25:19,651 --> 00:25:22,119
You posed as Kosei Neo

486
00:25:22,120 --> 00:25:23,754
to close the deal

487
00:25:23,755 --> 00:25:27,192
with Shino Real Estate. You can do this.

488
00:25:28,326 --> 00:25:29,361
But

489
00:25:30,128 --> 00:25:31,830
their relationship has soured…

490
00:25:33,298 --> 00:25:35,766
If you want to protect
the shopping street,

491
00:25:35,767 --> 00:25:37,402
this is your only choice.

492
00:25:40,939 --> 00:25:44,675
What happened
between President Neo and Shijo?

493
00:25:44,676 --> 00:25:45,610
Do you know?

494
00:25:46,411 --> 00:25:48,212
According to Tomono,

495
00:25:48,213 --> 00:25:49,680
their relationship broke off

496
00:25:49,681 --> 00:25:51,315
after the semiconductor venture,

497
00:25:51,316 --> 00:25:52,884
but he doesn't know the details.

498
00:25:55,186 --> 00:25:58,323
Going in blind, then.

499
00:26:07,232 --> 00:26:08,466
Shijo.

500
00:26:09,434 --> 00:26:10,334
It's been a while.

501
00:26:10,335 --> 00:26:12,904
I’ve been declining
unnecessary meetings since COVID, but…

502
00:26:23,181 --> 00:26:24,149
Actually,

503
00:26:25,317 --> 00:26:27,217
I’d like to buy a piece of land from you.

504
00:26:27,218 --> 00:26:28,920
I don’t intend to do business with you.

505
00:26:31,923 --> 00:26:32,891
Would…

506
00:26:34,392 --> 00:26:36,628
you tell me why?

507
00:26:41,132 --> 00:26:42,534
You really don't know?

508
00:26:45,971 --> 00:26:47,872
Sorry. Please tell me.

509
00:26:52,644 --> 00:26:54,812
Do you remember
when you were founding NEOXIS

510
00:26:54,813 --> 00:26:57,414
and I provided the funding

511
00:26:57,415 --> 00:26:58,783
and introduced you to Togo?

512
00:26:59,351 --> 00:27:02,419
Of course.
I'll never forget what you did for me.

513
00:27:02,420 --> 00:27:05,789
At that time, you told me,
"If you ever need help,

514
00:27:05,790 --> 00:27:10,227
I will always be there. Just ask."

515
00:27:10,228 --> 00:27:11,996
I remember that too.

516
00:27:11,997 --> 00:27:14,466
Then why didn't you keep your word?!

517
00:27:20,005 --> 00:27:22,206
When I came to you
in desperate need of a loan,

518
00:27:22,207 --> 00:27:24,408
you were consumed
by the semiconductor venture

519
00:27:24,409 --> 00:27:26,945
and turned me away cold.

520
00:27:30,548 --> 00:27:31,549
I…

521
00:27:33,451 --> 00:27:35,953
I must not have had the capacity then.

522
00:27:35,954 --> 00:27:37,055
Please forgive me.

523
00:27:37,622 --> 00:27:39,857
"Please forgive me"?

524
00:27:39,858 --> 00:27:41,159
Don’t act like it’s not your problem!

525
00:27:43,995 --> 00:27:45,996
At that time, I was thinking

526
00:27:45,997 --> 00:27:49,233
of nothing but becoming
the industry leader

527
00:27:49,234 --> 00:27:52,136
to protect my employees
and their families.

528
00:27:52,137 --> 00:27:55,072
I believed that would ultimately lead

529
00:27:55,073 --> 00:27:56,107
to contributing to society.

530
00:27:56,708 --> 00:27:58,108
Since then,

531
00:27:58,109 --> 00:28:00,678
you’ve no longer been
the Kosei Neo I first met.

532
00:28:00,679 --> 00:28:03,113
Arrogantly bragging that

533
00:28:03,114 --> 00:28:05,516
you spotted the semiconductor opportunity

534
00:28:05,517 --> 00:28:08,152
and that you foresaw Trump's victory…

535
00:28:08,153 --> 00:28:10,788
You became the well-known,
one-man operator of a company.

536
00:28:10,789 --> 00:28:11,723
On top of that,

537
00:28:12,257 --> 00:28:16,260
you ignored the counsel of Tomono,
a trusted voice from your founding days,

538
00:28:16,261 --> 00:28:18,530
and neglected your welfare mission.

539
00:28:20,899 --> 00:28:22,100
All I wanted was

540
00:28:23,435 --> 00:28:24,803
to protect the company…

541
00:28:25,370 --> 00:28:28,540
And so you said you had no time
to help others.

542
00:28:32,310 --> 00:28:33,778
I'm deeply ashamed.

543
00:28:36,014 --> 00:28:37,715
I know no apology

544
00:28:37,716 --> 00:28:40,719
can make this right. But…

545
00:28:41,386 --> 00:28:44,556
But I want to apologize.

546
00:28:46,925 --> 00:28:50,061
From the bottom of my heart,
I want to apologize.

547
00:28:50,795 --> 00:28:52,597
I repaid your kindness

548
00:28:53,498 --> 00:28:55,233
with the worst possible betrayal.

549
00:28:57,836 --> 00:28:59,571
I am truly, deeply sorry.

550
00:29:25,530 --> 00:29:26,998
Who are you?

551
00:29:29,567 --> 00:29:32,169
At the very least, the Kosei Neo I knew

552
00:29:32,170 --> 00:29:34,072
would never put on
a performance like this.

553
00:29:35,073 --> 00:29:36,573
And I'm not foolish enough

554
00:29:36,574 --> 00:29:39,210
to be taken in by such an act.

555
00:29:40,111 --> 00:29:41,880
Don't take me for a fool.

556
00:29:52,857 --> 00:29:54,959
AKARI-NU

557
00:29:56,361 --> 00:30:00,365
CONGRATS! SARASA IKETANI
LUMIÈRE INTERNATIONAL PAINTING COMPETITION

558
00:30:06,204 --> 00:30:08,206
CONGRATS! SARASA IKETANI
GOLD AWARD

559
00:30:42,407 --> 00:30:45,243
<i>History must be changed.</i>

560
00:31:17,575 --> 00:31:20,644
<i>I kept searching for land after that,</i>

561
00:31:20,645 --> 00:31:22,180
<i>but nothing came of it.</i>

562
00:31:24,182 --> 00:31:25,049
<i>My deadline</i>

563
00:31:25,750 --> 00:31:29,386
<i>of July 9th, 2022,</i>

564
00:31:29,387 --> 00:31:30,555
<i>was drawing near.</i>

565
00:31:34,225 --> 00:31:35,993
Vena Holdings

566
00:31:35,994 --> 00:31:37,895
is pushing hard
for the Akari Housing Complex

567
00:31:37,896 --> 00:31:39,631
and Akari Shopping Street.

568
00:31:40,431 --> 00:31:42,766
<i>No matter what I do,</i>

569
00:31:42,767 --> 00:31:44,702
<i>can I really not change history?</i>

570
00:31:50,441 --> 00:31:52,010
I have a request.

571
00:31:54,545 --> 00:31:55,580
Can you arrange

572
00:31:56,314 --> 00:31:59,050
a meeting with President Neo?

573
00:31:59,951 --> 00:32:02,320
That may be difficult.

574
00:32:03,354 --> 00:32:04,389
Why?

575
00:32:05,089 --> 00:32:07,391
He should at least meet me once

576
00:32:07,392 --> 00:32:09,360
before closing the building deal.

577
00:32:10,395 --> 00:32:12,129
President Neo

578
00:32:12,130 --> 00:32:14,499
may be deliberately avoiding you.

579
00:32:15,733 --> 00:32:18,136
<i>I'm avoiding myself?</i>

580
00:32:19,003 --> 00:32:20,804
He insists

581
00:32:20,805 --> 00:32:23,741
your ideas were his own.

582
00:32:24,342 --> 00:32:27,344
It's as if he fears his charisma

583
00:32:27,345 --> 00:32:30,281
could be diminished by someone else.

584
00:32:32,583 --> 00:32:33,685
So to President Neo,

585
00:32:35,219 --> 00:32:37,689
I'm nothing but an obstacle?

586
00:32:43,394 --> 00:32:44,362
And you've suffered,

587
00:32:45,463 --> 00:32:48,766
haven't you, Tomono?

588
00:32:52,503 --> 00:32:54,772
You really are kind, Eito.

589
00:32:57,809 --> 00:33:00,511
You are just like when I first met him.

590
00:33:07,251 --> 00:33:08,151
<i>In the end…</i>

591
00:33:08,152 --> 00:33:09,219
CONGRATS! SARASA IKETANI
LUMIÈRE INTERNATIONAL PAINTING COMPETITION

592
00:33:09,220 --> 00:33:12,657
<i>…the same thing is about to happen
as in my past timeline.</i>

593
00:33:14,225 --> 00:33:17,094
<i>But unlike in my past life,</i>

594
00:33:17,095 --> 00:33:19,297
<i>the shopping street has savings.</i>

595
00:33:21,032 --> 00:33:24,936
<i>If I prepare in advance
so they can resist the eviction…</i>

596
00:33:29,040 --> 00:33:32,043
CHAPTER 10
SUCCESS AND ITS COST

597
00:33:32,944 --> 00:33:35,879
THOSE WHO CHANGED HISTORY AND ACHIEVED
SUCCESS WILL HAVE TO PAY THE PRICE

598
00:33:35,880 --> 00:33:37,582
<i>The price is</i>

599
00:33:38,349 --> 00:33:39,550
<i>one's life.</i>

600
00:33:49,394 --> 00:33:50,361
Dad.

601
00:33:50,962 --> 00:33:51,796
Sorry.

602
00:33:52,563 --> 00:33:54,766
I know you're opening now,

603
00:33:56,367 --> 00:34:00,271
but I need you to hear me out
as president of the Akari Shopping Street.

604
00:34:02,407 --> 00:34:04,575
I want to discuss managing our assets

605
00:34:05,143 --> 00:34:07,779
through stock investments
for Akari Shopping Street's future.

606
00:34:10,848 --> 00:34:11,949
Are you listening, Dad?

607
00:34:18,823 --> 00:34:20,224
It's important.

608
00:34:23,594 --> 00:34:24,595
What's wrong?

609
00:34:28,066 --> 00:34:30,234
We're already invested in stocks.

610
00:34:31,302 --> 00:34:32,136
What?

611
00:34:33,237 --> 00:34:37,175
A foreign securities broker I met in Ginza
has been advising us.

612
00:34:39,510 --> 00:34:40,778
What kind of stocks?

613
00:34:42,413 --> 00:34:45,249
A pharmaceutical company
working on a COVID vaccine.

614
00:34:45,983 --> 00:34:49,220
Nice work, Dad!

615
00:34:49,787 --> 00:34:52,824
So, which company is it?

616
00:34:53,524 --> 00:34:56,160
China's Mao Pharma.

617
00:34:56,727 --> 00:34:58,129
Mao Pharma?

618
00:34:58,863 --> 00:35:00,131
Never heard of them.

619
00:35:00,998 --> 00:35:03,100
It's a Chinese company

620
00:35:03,101 --> 00:35:04,669
that was developing a vaccine.

621
00:35:05,603 --> 00:35:07,939
Was? They're not anymore?

622
00:35:08,506 --> 00:35:09,340
No.

623
00:35:11,442 --> 00:35:12,510
Why?

624
00:35:15,246 --> 00:35:16,581
Because they went bankrupt.

625
00:35:23,421 --> 00:35:26,491
I'm sorry, Eito. Please forgive me.

626
00:35:29,627 --> 00:35:31,629
All of Akari Shopping Street's savings…

627
00:35:33,698 --> 00:35:36,267
went into that investment…

628
00:35:38,970 --> 00:35:40,638
Then what about the revenue

629
00:35:42,173 --> 00:35:45,309
from the climate goods
and the COVID supplies?

630
00:35:47,078 --> 00:35:48,012
Gone.

631
00:35:50,148 --> 00:35:51,115
Don't tell me…

632
00:35:52,483 --> 00:35:55,520
My fees from Togo Fund

633
00:35:56,220 --> 00:35:59,857
and Sarasa's NEOXIS commercial earnings?

634
00:36:00,958 --> 00:36:02,360
All of it! Gone!

635
00:36:05,396 --> 00:36:06,397
At this point,

636
00:36:06,964 --> 00:36:08,698
the Akari Shopping Street

637
00:36:08,699 --> 00:36:12,436
has no funds left to invest.

638
00:36:44,202 --> 00:36:46,603
<i>If they push for eviction now,</i>

639
00:36:46,604 --> 00:36:48,773
<i>the shopping street has no chance.</i>

640
00:36:49,941 --> 00:36:52,576
<i>I want to confront Kosei Neo directly,</i>

641
00:36:52,577 --> 00:36:54,245
<i>but he's avoiding me.</i>

642
00:36:59,383 --> 00:37:00,518
<i>What can I do?</i>

643
00:37:12,096 --> 00:37:12,964
Sarasa.

644
00:37:21,472 --> 00:37:24,242
I need you to go see Kosei Neo.

645
00:37:35,586 --> 00:37:37,388
You want me to help
the Akari Shopping Street?

646
00:37:41,392 --> 00:37:42,226
Yes.

647
00:37:43,427 --> 00:37:44,262
So

648
00:37:45,496 --> 00:37:46,764
who put you up to this?

649
00:37:49,934 --> 00:37:53,204
Was it Eito Nomoto?

650
00:37:58,009 --> 00:37:59,076
Yes.

651
00:38:01,746 --> 00:38:03,347
What does he mean

652
00:38:04,382 --> 00:38:07,718
to you?

653
00:38:14,058 --> 00:38:17,027
He's someone who genuinely wants me
to be happy

654
00:38:17,028 --> 00:38:18,896
and cheers me on.

655
00:38:21,465 --> 00:38:22,300
That's wrong.

656
00:38:27,505 --> 00:38:28,606
He is not the one.

657
00:38:31,442 --> 00:38:33,577
What are you trying to say?

658
00:38:34,812 --> 00:38:36,814
Who was it that brought

659
00:38:37,848 --> 00:38:40,818
your existence to the world's attention?

660
00:38:43,454 --> 00:38:45,288
Are you saying you did something

661
00:38:45,289 --> 00:38:47,390
to help me win the award?

662
00:38:47,391 --> 00:38:50,828
I believe I may have
at least created the opportunity.

663
00:38:59,470 --> 00:39:02,139
Did you think that would make me happy?

664
00:39:05,176 --> 00:39:06,610
The person who taught me

665
00:39:07,345 --> 00:39:10,314
the joy of painting matters more to me…

666
00:39:14,852 --> 00:39:16,687
than any award.

667
00:39:47,518 --> 00:39:48,352
This…

668
00:39:50,054 --> 00:39:51,889
is my personal contact information.

669
00:40:02,066 --> 00:40:03,634
Contact me anytime.

670
00:40:08,406 --> 00:40:09,240
I'll…

671
00:40:11,242 --> 00:40:12,243
be waiting.

672
00:40:36,767 --> 00:40:37,902
Excuse me.

673
00:40:46,644 --> 00:40:49,012
<i>Following the death
of former Prime Minister Shinzo Abe,</i>

674
00:40:49,013 --> 00:40:52,082
<i>who was shot during a campaign speech,</i>

675
00:40:52,583 --> 00:40:53,483
<i>condolences have poured in</i>

676
00:40:53,484 --> 00:40:56,553
- <i>from world leaders.</i>
- <i>And that day finally arrived.</i>

677
00:40:56,554 --> 00:40:59,356
I'd like to reach a final decision.

678
00:41:01,058 --> 00:41:03,927
The only sites that meet
Vena Holdings' requirements

679
00:41:03,928 --> 00:41:06,463
are the Akari Housing Complex
and the Akari Shopping Street.

680
00:41:06,464 --> 00:41:07,798
I object.

681
00:41:08,299 --> 00:41:09,866
Eri is your secretary,

682
00:41:09,867 --> 00:41:12,402
and Sarasa is the face of our advertising.

683
00:41:12,403 --> 00:41:15,872
Destroying the shopping street
they live in is unthinkable.

684
00:41:15,873 --> 00:41:19,108
Since when did you become
a supporter of the shopping street?

685
00:41:19,109 --> 00:41:22,512
I've watched the Akari Shopping Street
work hard.

686
00:41:22,513 --> 00:41:26,182
We even partnered with them online
for the climate goods.

687
00:41:26,183 --> 00:41:28,485
But no matter how much support we give,

688
00:41:28,486 --> 00:41:30,621
that shopping street
is headed toward collapse anyway.

689
00:41:31,956 --> 00:41:33,090
Wouldn't NEOXIS

690
00:41:33,691 --> 00:41:35,625
continuing to grow
do more good for more people

691
00:41:35,626 --> 00:41:37,962
than preserving that place?

692
00:41:41,232 --> 00:41:43,600
Then it's decided. The acquisition site

693
00:41:43,601 --> 00:41:46,804
will be the Akari Housing Complex
and the Akari Shopping Street.

694
00:41:49,273 --> 00:41:51,708
Tsuchiya and Takarabe.

695
00:41:51,709 --> 00:41:54,411
Please handle
the Akari Housing Complex eviction.

696
00:41:54,912 --> 00:41:57,081
- Yes.
- For Tomono,

697
00:41:58,282 --> 00:41:59,682
I'd like you to handle

698
00:41:59,683 --> 00:42:01,952
the shopping street negotiations.

699
00:42:03,320 --> 00:42:04,955
It's a job only you can do.

700
00:42:05,756 --> 00:42:08,826
It might as well have been made for you.

701
00:42:11,629 --> 00:42:13,764
It seems you're also close
with my secretary.

702
00:42:17,134 --> 00:42:20,371
And if I were to refuse?

703
00:42:24,308 --> 00:42:27,144
Your father is seriously ill

704
00:42:28,312 --> 00:42:30,247
and struggling with medical bills,
isn't he?

705
00:42:34,084 --> 00:42:36,320
Leave the company now,

706
00:42:37,454 --> 00:42:39,356
or help the company grow.

707
00:42:41,058 --> 00:42:42,426
The answer is obvious, isn't it?

708
00:42:59,577 --> 00:43:00,544
AKARI-NU

709
00:43:08,152 --> 00:43:09,086
I've come today

710
00:43:09,753 --> 00:43:12,056
to deliver important news.

711
00:43:16,126 --> 00:43:19,563
NEOXIS is acquiring Akari Shopping Street.

712
00:43:21,565 --> 00:43:22,533
I'll be

713
00:43:23,467 --> 00:43:25,302
leading that effort,

714
00:43:25,903 --> 00:43:28,939
which means I'll be on the opposing side
from everyone here.

715
00:43:30,741 --> 00:43:32,209
President Neo may have thought

716
00:43:32,843 --> 00:43:35,311
that with me in charge,

717
00:43:35,312 --> 00:43:39,782
the negotiations could be handled

718
00:43:39,783 --> 00:43:41,751
with more care for the shopping street.

719
00:43:41,752 --> 00:43:43,354
I want to believe that.

720
00:43:44,688 --> 00:43:45,522
But…

721
00:43:47,057 --> 00:43:48,258
But if this is meant…

722
00:43:50,928 --> 00:43:54,398
as some kind of harassment for you and me…

723
00:43:58,769 --> 00:44:01,271
I will never forgive President Neo.

724
00:44:08,412 --> 00:44:09,346
<i>Could it have been…</i>

725
00:44:16,253 --> 00:44:17,821
<i>Tomono?</i>

726
00:44:18,989 --> 00:44:19,589
‎NEXT PREVIEW
‎THE CYCLE OF TRAGEDY CONTINUES

727
00:44:19,590 --> 00:44:21,491
‎-Eviction?
‎-Are you telling us to get out?

728
00:44:21,492 --> 00:44:22,892
‎Give me a break!

729
00:44:22,893 --> 00:44:26,596
<i>‎At this rate,
‎we’ll be headed down a tragic path.</i>

730
00:44:26,597 --> 00:44:28,398
‎Not everyone is controlled by money.

731
00:44:28,399 --> 00:44:29,999
‎I want to save Akari Shopping Street.

732
00:44:30,000 --> 00:44:31,901
<i>‎Could it be Sarasa…?</i>

733
00:44:31,902 --> 00:44:33,336
‎We’ve just got to enjoy it, right?

734
00:44:33,337 --> 00:44:34,003
‎A NEW SUSPECT EMERGES
‎THIS DRAMA IS FICTION

735
00:44:34,004 --> 00:44:34,972
Subtitle translation by: Ken Nishizaki
